{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Saga does its work in multiple stages."}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, it finds all the files within the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"input"},{"type":"text","text":" folder"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, for every registered step, it passes those files to a matching "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Saga\/documentation\/Saga\/Reader"},{"type":"text","text":". These readers turn text files (such as Markdown or RestructuredText files) into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Item"},{"type":"text","text":" instances."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally Saga runs all the registered steps again, now executing the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Saga\/documentation\/Saga\/Writer"},{"type":"text","text":"s. These writers turn a rendering context (which holds the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Saga\/documentation\/Saga\/Item"},{"type":"text","text":" among other things) into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" using a “renderer”, which it’ll then write to disk, to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"output"},{"type":"text","text":" folder."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Saga does not come with any readers or renderers out of the box. The official recommendation is to use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/loopwerk\/SagaParsleyMarkdownReader"},{"type":"text","text":" for reading Markdown files using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/loopwerk\/Parsley"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"ty